The paper deals with deep neural network architectures for information extraction in document images, specifically for text localization, transcription, and named entity recognition. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of shared features for these tasks, which could also relate to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories.
